  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Organisational Progress for Bees for Development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We provide information and capacity building to make beekeeping enterprises viable and sustainable. Our activities link beekeepers with published and unpublished information, experiential learning, and the practical resources needed to undertake training in remote places. The work is complex, multi-faceted and dependent on high levels of personal knowledge and skill among BfD staff and network members. Our network is international, focussed on disseminating vital information to beekeepers in poor and remote places, often with no intermediary, national associations. We recognise that expansion of our work demands attention to the strategic development of the organisation, to maximise impact and effectiveness. We want to develop our network strategy, information management and communications. We want to increase our skills in managing the diverse materials that make up the international knowledge base of sustainable beekeeping, and underpin this resource with appropriate, efficient and accessible technology. We need to publicise this knowledge more widely and demonstrate its impact. BfD provides a real and valued service to beekeepers. We believe that by developing our communications strategy we can create impact beyond the beekeeping world, to achieve wider recognition of the role of apiculture, to leverage better support for beekeepers in marginalised communities.</narrative>
  </description>
